## Positioning logic

```js
function positionMenu(menuEl, boundsGroupId, centerX, topY, bottomY) { ... }
```

1. Get the selection's bounding coordinates via `view.coordsAtPos(from)` and
   `view.coordsAtPos(to)` — these are real viewport coordinates of where the selected
   text starts/ends.
2. Center the menu horizontally on the midpoint of the selection.
3. **Clamp horizontally** so the menu can never overflow past `minX`/`maxX`. By default
   these are the window edges (with 8px padding). If a `boundsGroupId` element exists
   (an element whose ID matches `BOUNDS_GROUP_ID_PREFIX + index`), its
   `getBoundingClientRect()` left/right values are used instead — so the menu is
   constrained to stay within that specific element's width instead of the whole
   screen. In this setup, `BOUNDS_GROUP_ID_PREFIX` is set to the same value as
   `WRAPPER_ID_PREFIX`, so the menu is bounded by the Tiptap input's own width.
4. **Vertical placement**: normally shown 8px above the selection. If there isn't
   enough room above (too close to the top of the viewport), it flips to show 8px
   below the selection instead.

